FIG. 1 is a partial side elevation, partially sectioned, of two thermoplastic members of a filter assembly to be connected together as a fusion welded thermoplastic assembly in accordance with principles of the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a side elevation, partially sectioned, of the two components of FIG. 1 operatively coupled to one another and a thermoplastic fusion ring with a heater platen disposed therebetween, illustrating the method of the present invention;


FIG. 3 is a side elevation, partially sectioned, of the two components of FIG. 1 connected to one another by the thermoplastic fusion element to form a thermoplastic fusion assembly according to the present invention;


FIG. 4 is a side elevation, partially sectioned, of three components of a filter cartridge assembly to be connected together as a fusion-welded thermoplastic assembly in accordance with principles of the present invention;


FIG. 5 is an enlarged view of the area within circle "V" in FIG. 4; and


FIG. 6 is a side elevation, in cross-section, illustrating the difficulties encountered in fusion-welding components having mating surfaces that are recessed with respect to other surfaces.
